From ab5fd3ad063db428938f985404a210437e8ea889 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ci <ci@local>
Date: Sat, 16 May 2026 00:29:15 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] net: dpaa: advertise NETIF_F_HW_TC for nft flowtable offload

PR14g-body-1: completes the wiring from 0002 + 0028. Without
NETIF_F_HW_TC in dev->features, nf_flow_offload_tuple() silently
falls back to software (every packet rides the kernel softpath
and CPU pins at ~50%% at multi-Gbps line rates).

With this bit set, nft flowtable offload reaches dpaa_setup_tc()
which dispatches to ask.ko, which programs the FMan PCD chain.
No behaviour change when ask.ko is not loaded (dispatcher slot
empty -> -EOPNOTSUPP -> SW fallback as before).

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <ask20@vyos-ls1046a-build>

---
 drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
index b6b7316..38ed9ae 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
@@ -233,6 +233,15 @@ static int dpaa_netdev_init(struct net_device *net_dev,
 				 NETIF_F_RXHASH);
 
 	net_dev->hw_features |= NETIF_F_SG | NETIF_F_HIGHDMA;
+
+	/* ASK2 — advertise NETIF_F_HW_TC so nft flowtable offload
+	 * (nf_flow_table_offload.c::nf_flow_offload_tuple) will push
+	 * flows to hardware via dpaa_setup_tc(). If no backend has
+	 * registered via dpaa_register_flow_offload_handler(), the
+	 * dispatch returns -EOPNOTSUPP and the upper layer falls
+	 * back to software flow_offload.
+	 */
+	net_dev->hw_features |= NETIF_F_HW_TC;
 	/* The kernels enables GSO automatically, if we declare NETIF_F_SG.
 	 * For conformity, we'll still declare GSO explicitly.
 	 */
